Comment: 0,0:20:24.47,0:20:24.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.91,0:20:29.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.44,0:20:32.90,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.90,0:20:36.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.62,0:20:39.53,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.75,0:20:51.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.17,0:20:54.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.93,0:20:58.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.47,0:21:01.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.31,0:21:05.04,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.89,0:21:08.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.44,0:21:12.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.99,0:21:17.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.69,0:21:22.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.34,0:21:25.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams: {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.75,0:21:29.38,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.38,0:21:32.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.20,0:21:36.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.97,0:21:40.38,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, I'll do my best to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:43.97,0:21:43.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.47,0:00:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,With Annie's instigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.85,0:00:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the mini-concert at school \Nis to be held with Luise in the vanguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.19,0:00:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Alas, the girl doesn't know \Nthe first thing about playing the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.74,0:00:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Being at a complete loss, Luise \Ntried to reach out to Lotte via the phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.61,0:00:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but this time, nobody answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.98,0:00:29.05,Sign,,0,0,120,,{\c&HBAFCFD&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 15 \N {\fs35} Lotte, Help! \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.62,0:01:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte being able to play piano \Nwas one big lie all along!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.62,0:01:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte screwed everyone over! She is a liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.96,0:01:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.82,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, help!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.84,0:01:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.20,0:01:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte? Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.70,0:01:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.41,0:01:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.60,0:01:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You were moaning in your sleep. {to cry out in one's sleep (e.g. from having a nightmare); to moan (in anguish) in one's sleep}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.14,0:01:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have a fever, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.60,0:01:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.04,0:01:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just had a slightly unpleasant dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.95,0:01:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... Glad to know it's nothing serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.89,0:01:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, come on, wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.70,0:01:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take care of the breakfast today, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.17,0:01:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.89,0:01:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Slightly unpleasant" doesn't do it justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.83,0:01:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, Lotte, where could you have gone to?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.79,0:01:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody in the house to even answer the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.16,0:02:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.08,0:02:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you come here for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.80,0:02:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.78,0:02:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How about this, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.00,0:02:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, mom? This...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.29,0:02:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought, you need to look appropriately \Nfor today's concert, so I bought this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.16,0:02:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's just a mini-concert in school, \Nit'd be wiser not to spend too much on it... {waste (of money, time, etc.); squandering; frittering away}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.81,0:02:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind that, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.42,0:02:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't concern yourself with such matters, \Njust do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.47,0:02:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I'm deep in trouble. \NRunning away is getting too difficult to pull off!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.18,0:02:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try to leave early today to cheer you on. {leaving work (office, school) early}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.85,0:02:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sure, Editor Bernau \Nwould love to come listen to it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.52,0:02:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let him down!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.76,0:02:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You're relying too much on me! {unsure what she means: exaggerated; overdone; overblown; hyperbolic; bombastic; grandiose}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.41,0:02:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I've just barely renewed the practice,\Nand I still make a lot of rookie mistakes! {/couldn't practice enough as of late, It'll be embarrassing to make a mistake}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's better if he doesn't come! {/it's fine if he doesn't come}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.42,0:02:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I know my Lotte would handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:02:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistakes won't blemish a talent such as yours. {/because you have ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.34,0:03:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave this in the bedroom, \Nso once the classes are over, come and change. {and go out again}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.57,0:03:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Malingering is still an option for me, \Nbut that'd be a dead giveaway to mom. {/upset mom beyond belief.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.47,0:03:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... What can I even do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.62,0:03:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Alps, the temperature \Nremains rather low even in the summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.22,0:03:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so countless clusters of perpetual snow \Neventually form into glaciers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.85,0:03:31.69,Sign,,0,0,0,,Germany is located exactly to the north \Nfrom the main alpine ridge. {guess, "doitsu kono dai alpen no ichiban ??? atarimasu"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.72,0:03:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Things turned from bad to worse. {guess, hear zettai ... pinchi there}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.69,0:03:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I talk my way out of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.69,0:03:38.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,Consequently, the highest peak on the German side of it - \Nresting at 2,963 meters, Zugspitze.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.72,0:03:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All this is happening to me \Nbecause of Annie's stupid instigation! {/said too much}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.76,0:03:43.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,It is a popular attraction for ski enthusiasts, \Nthat climb to the top in a cable car.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.17,0:03:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.34,0:03:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you need to calm down a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.28,0:03:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, the mini-concert this afternoon \Nwould be attended by the principal, as well as many parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You should refrain from misbehavior. {vulgar; crude; tacky​}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.79,0:03:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.73,0:04:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.63,0:04:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm excited to hear your mini-concert today!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.74,0:04:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Okay. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.47,0:04:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You think she'll dare to show up for the mini-concert?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.21,0:04:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the point of showing up \Nif she can't play? {unsure, maybe she means "if she doesn't, that's fine by us too"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.78,0:04:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, how do you think, \Nwhat'll Lotte do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.15,0:04:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you have done in her shoes? {no clue what's the first word, would assume it's her name even though it's nowhere near miria.... as if her name wasn't enough an enigma before, ffs}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.42,0:04:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd try to make a run for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.50,0:04:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She might pretend to fall ill, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.98,0:04:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're here to prevent any of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.04,0:04:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever she tries to pull, we'll expose Lotte! \NShe'll bear the brunt of {the grand }embarrassment! {/pull lotte out}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.48,0:05:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be because Annie \Nalso suspects I'm not the real Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.92,0:05:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But she doesn't have any reason to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.38,0:05:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this doesn't help... {depression; melancholy; dejection; gloom; despondency}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.30,0:05:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.67,0:05:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, you can't tell? It's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,See? None other, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.00,0:05:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.07,0:05:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the real one at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.13,0:05:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a saver!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.61,0:05:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Saver from what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.64,0:05:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.30,0:05:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad, Annie is still on my tail. {/will find you}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.88,0:05:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.52,0:05:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Put on your mask, Lotte! {disguise; masquerade}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.89,0:05:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be some of Lotte's friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.55,0:05:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Where could I have seen her... {usually, this phrase is used in the meaning "since when did you" so she likely means "at which point did she meet lotte" but I can't make it work :(}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.84,0:06:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowhere to hide around this place. \NAnnie and others won't be able to get close.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.81,0:06:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That sure was startling. \NYou materialized in front of me out of thin air!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.88,0:06:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was you who didn't show up \Nfor the rendezvous. {/didn't come at the appointed place}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.41,0:06:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to intercept you on the way. {/I came}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.06,0:06:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What rendezvous?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The one I appointed in the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.27,0:06:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.53,0:06:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Those few days were so hectic, \NI forgot about checking in the post office! {to get a fright; to panic; to get flustered; to be startled}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.53,0:06:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My, Luise, you're always like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.04,0:06:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hear this, dad recently got an offer \Nto conduct the Munich Symphony Orchestra!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.10,0:06:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So he brought me along!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.49,0:06:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Dad is also here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.21,0:06:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why nobody was answering \Nyour phone in Vienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.41,0:06:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The phone? Did something urgent happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.59,0:06:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother of all urgencies! \NI got myself involved in something big.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.62,0:06:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Something big?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.91,0:06:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, we're in the clear - \NLotte showed up to save the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.33,0:06:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a godsend!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.90,0:06:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.50,0:06:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What could they be talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.58,0:07:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the way they cuddle each other,\Nyou'd think they've a foot in both camps! {REALLY fucking hope it's "jinkaku utagacchaimasu" and not "chigaimasu", but still that'd only mean "when two/fellow women are hugging each other, they are questioning/doubting/suspecting their personality/character" and I can't find "人格疑る" being used in the sense of "lesbian/gender/nature" and only tangentally "personality disorder" so... really fucking at a loss, if they don't mean "lesbians" that'd be a big fucking blunder, and vice versa}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.84,0:07:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What's having a foot in both camps?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.42,0:07:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.48,0:07:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If I knew, I wouldn't be asking!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.75,0:07:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really get it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.14,0:07:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Gosh, you're useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.51,0:07:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No "rewrite it once again?" {actually she just says "rewrite again" but I think she means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.53,0:07:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, it's good enough as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.68,0:07:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My, how peculiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.99,0:07:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope it doesn't snow today. {I was sure there's an analogous idiom for that in english, but apparently not }
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.86,0:07:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The event is peculiar indeed, \Nso you'd better be sincerely glad about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.91,0:07:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, will do hereafter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.34,0:07:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Your next assignment would be \Nthe field work at the Munich Philharmonic. {/collecting data about Munich Symphony Orchestra}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.94,0:07:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm told, for the upcoming series of concerts, the same Palfy \Nwe discussed before, had come to do the conducting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.52,0:07:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He is currently in Munich?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.85,0:07:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,His previous performance in Berlin - \Nwhy was it cancelled?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.79,0:07:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he regret letting down the audience \Nthat has been waiting for him eagerly? {/didn't he disregard ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.25,0:07:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you \Nto unravel those mysteries. {/collect data on that topic}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.73,0:07:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.36,0:08:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? A mini-concert on piano?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.37,0:08:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You must really feel troubled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.25,0:08:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,To the point of seeing nightmares about it! I was already \Nconsidering coming clean and just returning to Vienna. {/I was even crying in my sleep} {horidasu is "to dig out; to pick up" and i dunno what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.20,0:08:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, the true Lotte is also here, \Nso we're on the right path again! {/everything is resolved}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.95,0:08:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, we just need to exchange places again, \Nin a way inconspicuous to Annie. {and her bunch, who are onto something/have a clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.52,0:08:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But say, isn't it weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.18,0:08:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte no longer looks troubled!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.09,0:08:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm! Must be just pretending. {enduring something out of pride; putting up with it; grinning and bearing it}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.68,0:08:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, Lotte isn't running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.71,0:08:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't know for sure yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.40,0:08:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Not until she comes out and goes there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.26,0:09:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But if she doesn't, I'll drag her there, even if by the hair! \NYou're playing piano today, like it or not! {/and make her play piano}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.59,0:09:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, what is dad up to now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.43,0:09:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Went to the theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.32,0:09:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He expects me to return to the hotel by six.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.74,0:09:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Mini-concert starts at three, \Nso you'll have plenty of time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.28,0:09:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.33,0:09:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're done making the braids, change into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.92,0:09:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom even bought such a pretty dress for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.82,0:09:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm too embarrassed to wear it myself. {/a waste}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.87,0:09:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I can always go there myself \Nand play the piano to the best of my abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.62,0:09:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Editor, if Lotte is still home, \NI'll invite her to go with us. {hope this is what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.69,0:09:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, we'll wait for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.84,0:09:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte's mom here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.94,0:09:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, Lotte it out of options for running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.53,0:09:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Told you, she'll feign a sickness at the last moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.87,0:10:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if she does, I'll make sure everyone knows: \Nher only real disease is her inability to play the piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.47,0:10:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks good, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.93,0:10:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.03,0:10:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Like it was cut out for you! {/fits well}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.40,0:10:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, are you still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.21,0:10:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We came to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.30,0:10:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! Mom returned home!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.31,0:10:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.63,0:10:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you leave already?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.15,0:10:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, quick, hide under the bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.92,0:10:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, why should I be the one hiding?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.23,0:10:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.89,0:10:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Luise again, and you're Lotte now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.22,0:10:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Not here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.11,0:10:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.59,0:10:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick! Quick, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.30,0:10:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.01,0:10:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.44,0:11:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? There! My pen fell into under the bed. \NNeeded to pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.44,0:11:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But I could have sworn, in the hallway, \NI heard you talking now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.18,0:11:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that... I was just humming the tune \NI'm to play at the mini-concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.53,0:11:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.35,0:11:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, this dress you bought for me \Nis just gorgeous!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.15,0:11:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks becoming on you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.31,0:11:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.31,0:11:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.38,0:11:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Editor-in-Chief Bernau \Nis waiting for us in the taxi
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.36,0:11:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's set out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.96,0:11:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to finish just one more thing, \Ncan you go ahead?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.60,0:11:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, just make it quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.21,0:11:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.07,0:11:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you catch a cold, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.82,0:11:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't. It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.46,0:11:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.06,0:11:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.32,0:11:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.38,0:11:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, when the mini-concert is over, \Nmeet me at the science class, will you? {not really sure what to make of 理科室, maybe laboratory?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.70,0:11:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There, we'll change clothes again, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.71,0:11:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.27,0:12:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, see you there. {/I'm going}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.53,0:12:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez, that sure was close!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.70,0:12:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.70,0:12:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte is going there with her mom like it's nothing! {most likely "issho ni" tho sounds close to shujin - husband}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.69,0:12:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.11,0:12:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We should go too. {not really sure how this message differs from prev. line}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.08,0:12:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Maybe her plan is to make a run for it from school?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.90,0:12:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie sure is a diehard believer. {doubting; distrustful; incredulous; suspicious​}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.31,0:12:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong. This is called a tenacious disbeliever. {vindictive; tenacious; persistent; spiteful; vengeful} {not sure what;s the original joke here so I added my own one instead}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.55,0:12:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria, Miria, what are you waiting for? Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.27,0:12:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! On our way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.70,0:12:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do you know -\Nnobody noticed a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but that's for later. \NI need to get to school now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.30,0:13:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,While we're at it, your schedule for tomorrow: \N at ten - first round of rehearsals.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.33,0:13:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this sounds wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.20,0:13:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As expected of a genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.61,0:13:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Chauffeur, stop the car around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.43,0:13:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, from here on, I'll walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.63,0:13:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're free to return on wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.24,0:13:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Herr Palfy, \Nit's still quite the long way from the hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.81,0:13:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A strange town and a strange wind \Nare exceptional ingredients for making a good music. {/create just the mood for composing}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.62,0:13:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.78,0:13:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.71,0:13:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's totally strange - \Nshe doesn't seem to be running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.40,0:13:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she really going to play?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.44,0:14:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my sis Lotte! Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.41,0:15:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true what they say Lotte is good at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.58,0:15:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmpf! All she can do is play piano! \NHow can one be such a one-trick pony? {guess, hope its chittomo erabu}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.83,0:15:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,True. Playing the piano is the only thing she's good at.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.44,0:15:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I never had any idea Lotte was that talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.27,0:15:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She sounds like the first-class pianist already.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.50,0:15:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, you needn't exaggerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.34,0:15:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, that's what I really think.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.42,0:15:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, you can't deny she's gotten remarkably better. {dramatic (improvement); remarkable (difference); marked; noticeable}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.19,0:15:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How did she manage it even without practicing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.75,0:15:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, she inherited her dad's aptitude in full. {makings (of); aptitude; talent; qualities}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.58,0:15:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, this piano \Nsounds very alike to how he used to play it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.57,0:15:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where had I heard this play before... {/it's similar to whose playing}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.47,0:15:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.61,0:16:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like Luise's play!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.13,0:16:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, could it be? \NLuise is playing in a place like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.43,0:16:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.59,0:16:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea how good she was!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.16,0:16:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Alas, we'll have to exchange places again. \NI'm returning to my mom, and Lotte stays with dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.30,0:16:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I'll be waiting for you \Nin the science class, as planned. {/I'm going to}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.35,0:16:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Spectacular! {hope it's migoto }
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.58,0:16:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd never tell she is an elementary school student!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.95,0:16:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.63,0:16:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.26,0:17:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.93,0:17:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.25,0:17:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.14,0:17:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise! I knew it was you playing it all along!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.60,0:17:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Look, I can explain...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.04,0:17:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to explain something so good! {/whatever is the reason, it's fine}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.98,0:17:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Your gift is astonishing, that's all that matters!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.24,0:17:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! A professional pianist career \Nis what you should aim for! {aren't you aiming to be a full-scale; full-blown; all-out; full-fledged; fully fledged; full; proper; real; earnest; serious pianist}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.12,0:17:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! That's decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.98,0:17:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be deciding this for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.21,0:17:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we should celebrate with a good feast. {/grab something to eat somewhere} \NLet's return to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.44,0:17:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.47,0:17:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Lotte, what do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.70,0:17:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, this performance was something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.34,0:17:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.02,0:17:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you're really excited, aren't you? {excitement; stimulation; agitation; arousal}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.94,0:17:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can turn into such a child \Nin a matter of minute! {/spoiled child}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.59,0:17:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I do! {/because...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.93,0:18:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Terribly sorry to interrupt a precious intimate moment \Nof parent and child, but still, may I add something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.80,0:18:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief Bernau!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.56,0:18:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You really have a gift for that kind of thing.{/you play well} \NThe performance was fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.47,0:18:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.04,0:18:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my, you're not only graceful with piano, \Nbut your whole bearing had become thoroughly lady-like! {same way as elegant; graceful; refined with piano, even in manner; demeanour; demeanor; bearing, ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.38,0:18:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.94,0:18:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, Editor-in-Chief Bernau \Noffered to treat us to a delicious dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.86,0:18:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte's success today \Nought to be properly celebrated. {congratulation; congratulations; celebration; festival}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.69,0:18:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, pick anything you like from the menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.92,0:18:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Delightful! \NAre you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.52,0:18:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Most certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.19,0:18:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I'm supposed to be in the science class, \Nexchanging dresses with Luise right about now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.96,0:18:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, mom, please wait for me outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.50,0:18:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I just need to finish one more thing. {/settle the business}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.84,0:18:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.54,0:18:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, you've outdone yourself today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.78,0:18:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the best mini-concert we ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.76,0:19:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Frau Linnekogel. {from de}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.35,0:19:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, good job!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.69,0:19:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.10,0:19:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is Luise there with dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.02,0:19:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.65,0:19:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.57,0:19:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In a twist of fate that was considered inconceivable, \Nthings returned to normal:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.26,0:20:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise left with her dad, \Nand Lotte is going to live with her mom again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.97,0:20:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it'll be premature to assume \Nthings are staying this way for long. {to settle down (into); to be installed (in one's rightful place); to be returned (to one's original position)}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.32,0:20:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As fate would have it, both the twins and their parents \Nall happened to be in Munich.{/assembled/collected}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.88,0:20:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what else does fate have in store for them? {/will happen}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.32,0:21:45.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.64,0:21:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe it, Luise? \NI finally mustered enough courage to ask mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.81,0:21:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.85,0:21:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Editor Bernau and mom are getting along so well, \NI asked if they're considering a marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.22,0:21:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And what did mom say to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.22,0:22:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"I've had my share of marriage." {having had enough (of); fed up (with); sick and tired (of)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.96,0:22:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Dad told me the exact same thing! \NHe had his share of marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.07,0:22:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.33,0:22:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How come both gave the exact same answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.86,0:22:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.50,0:22:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Quirk of Fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.66,0:22:13.16,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 16\NQuirk of Fate {運命のいたずら}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.93,0:22:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't miss it!
